Fair and Unbiased Assessment System
Project Overview

The Fair and Unbiased Assessment System is an AI-based academic assessment and report generation system designed for educational institutions. The purpose of this project is to automate the assessment evaluation process, reduce human bias in grading, and provide detailed academic performance analysis for both students and faculty members.

The system allows students to upload assessment files in PDF format, while faculty members can manage assessments, monitor class performance, and view generated reports. Artificial intelligence is used to evaluate assessments and generate performance reports automatically.

This project mainly focuses on database design, academic workflow management, assessment tracking, enrollment management, and report generation within a university environment.

Features
User authentication and management
Student and faculty management
Department and program management
Batch, semester, session, and section handling
Course and teaching assignment management
Student enrollment management
Assessment creation and management
Student submission handling
AI-based evaluation processing
Student performance reports
Class performance reports
Historical academic record preservation
Activity logging and monitoring
System Modules
User Management

Manages user accounts, authentication, and role-based access for students and faculty members.

Academic Management

Handles departments, programs, batches, semesters, sessions, sections, and course structures.

Enrollment Management

Maintains student enrollment history, repeat-course handling, and course registration workflows.

Assessment Management

Allows faculty members to create quizzes, assignments, and assessment records.

Submission & Evaluation

Stores student submissions and AI-generated evaluation results including marks, percentages, and feedback.

Report Generation

Generates:

Student assessment reports
Class performance reports
AI-generated evaluation summaries
